<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Triceps Medial Head</h2>



<p>The medial head of the triceps brachii is located deeper in the arm than the other two muscles. It is located at the base of both the lateral and long heads. It originates at the back of the upper arm bone and connects to the elbow bone. </p>



<p>The medial head, like the other two heads, controls elbow extension. It is especially activated when the elbow is fully extended and helps to stabilize the joint.</p>


